From c6b43e160f2f8871b115ce640d363d55b0326205 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: RivonClaw CI <ci@rivonclaw.com>
Date: Wed, 8 Jul 2026 20:16:28 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] vendor(openclaw): run image tool prompts in child process

Why:

- RivonClaw customer-service workloads can trigger OpenClaw's built-in image tool on large or multi-image buyer messages.

- Running the image-model prompt path in the gateway process can block the event loop and saturate the main process CPU.

- RivonClaw needs to keep the official image tool name and capability semantics while isolating the heavy image prompt execution path.

- Worker startup and model runtime resolution must not consume the provider request timeout budget, otherwise cold workers reach the image model with only a few seconds remaining.

Removal:

- Drop when upstream OpenClaw runs image-tool media understanding outside the gateway event-loop process or exposes an equivalent worker-backed image tool execution option with provider-request timeout isolation.

Tests:

- vendor/openclaw/src/media-understanding/image.test.ts

- vendor/openclaw/src/agents/tools/image-tool.test.ts

- apps/desktop/src/cs-bridge/vendor-image-tool-worker.sentinel.test.ts
